      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OREGON JANET (7) had the drop on the lead from the inside before drawing clear to score (43.70) at Mt Gambier in a Special conditions race over 732m. Speedy runner who can find the front with a clear break from out wide. Hard to fault her form and she makes plenty of appeal. NITRO NEO (1) did a good job to finish third last time out over 732m at Mt Gambier (44.57) in a Special conditions race, the second top-three finish on the trot. With a good start should be able to take advantage of the rails draw. Can turn it around this time. NOVA'S FERN (5) continues to race well but is struggling to break through, placing at her last eight runs. Last start finished 2nd in a Grade 4/5 on June 8 over 530m at Angle Park behind Proclivity beaten 8 lengths (31.02). Has good box speed and can overcome the tricky draw. Can measure up. ZENVO YOYO (3) can fill a top-three spot.",
